"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"The native verification protocol is a protocol that is completely verified by the verifier of the underlying chain for the data passed between the chains. This is usually done by running a light client of one chain in the Ethereum Virtual Machine (VM) of another chain, and vice versa\\n\\nExamples include Cosmos IBC and NEAR RainbowBridge. Rollup entrance/exit is also a special form of it!\\n\\nAdvantage:\\n• No need to trust the highest degree of interoperability, because the underlying verifier is directly responsible for the security of the \\\"bridge\\\";\\n• Achieve completely universal messaging between domains.\\n\\nDisadvantages:\\n• Rely on the underlying trust and/or consensus mechanism of the domain to operate, so it must be customized for each type of domain.\\n\\nThe Ethereum ecosystem is highly heterogeneous: we have many domains, from zk/optimistic rollups to side chains, to the basic chain running various consensus algorithms: ETH-PoW, Nakamoto-PoW, Tendermint-PoS, Snowball-PoS , PoA, there are many consensus mechanisms. Each of these domains requires a unique strategy to implement a natively verified interoperability system.\",\"timestamp\":1634226969,\"title\":\"What is native verification?\"},\"digest\":\"IhO0z5rKQ9kPHfavas6bpP_HCe7gcKGNnA0CenVAqRE\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x68a78F3b7Ed88a22e5e158320e0d15B52eDFa312\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"MELojbZ9sKnP9amSMRT1v5x1sRPlmtwtnHRy2nBHVrg\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"IzPOwqnL1hxEkr28hsd1pM1EgzkGVDDsI-ZuE6xWTNM\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"qFr3ZFCmaaDoReMMsk_cVGPm9e4i9W_wF1JzBUrG1Dz6UG8hpAzGDpfFdMGtE52xzUjRAI1oHK7XSpo6aLQxjQ\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0xee8db46c39fe2833038078d2239ee192cea27fd1d7be0481c0606e0c84f56c62569bbd3b93ac34923f7ac6c446924615c8ccfe4e88bf684da94bb783e3fbbb851c\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv